49:34.369 --> 49:36.579
Oh, yeah.
You know who?

49:38.706 --> 49:40.500
What would Frank say?

49:42.877 --> 49:44.587
I like Frank,
you know?

49:45.088 --> 49:46.923
Only I like you better.

49:54.764 --> 49:55.932
You got some for me?

49:56.015 --> 49:57.100
Sure.

50:04.774 --> 50:05.942
Okay.

50:12.448 --> 50:13.574
Okay.

50:15.410 --> 50:18.037
Don't get confused, Tony.

50:18.121 --> 50:20.206
I don't fuck around
with the help.

50:27.755 --> 50:31.592
You wanna play that way with
me, I play with you.

50:31.718 --> 50:32.927
Shit.

50:33.553 --> 50:35.304
Would you kiss me
if I wear the hat?

50:35.388 --> 50:36.472
No!

50:38.725 --> 50:40.101
Playtime is over, okay?

50:43.646 --> 50:44.772
Okay.

51:38.159 --> 51:39.452
Mama?

51:41.204 --> 51:42.455
Antonio.

51:42.789 --> 51:44.040
Long time.

51:46.876 --> 51:48.628
No postcards
from jail, huh?

51:59.472 --> 52:00.640
Gina.

52:02.391 --> 52:03.810
Tony?

52:03.893 --> 52:05.228
Look at you.

52:07.146 --> 52:08.689
You're beautiful.

52:09.398 --> 52:10.399
I didn't...

52:10.483 --> 52:12.151
Mama, look at
those eyes, huh.

52:12.401 --> 52:13.986
Look at that.
She looks like me.

52:15.363 --> 52:18.241
You know the last time I saw
you, you was like that.

52:18.324 --> 52:21.828
You looked like a little boy.
Now look at you.

52:26.207 --> 52:28.084
I got something
for you.

52:33.214 --> 52:35.049
It's no big deal.

52:37.051 --> 52:38.052
Oh, Tony!

52:49.689 --> 52:51.941
I never thought I'd see you
again, you know?

52:52.066 --> 52:54.193
You think they'd keep
a guy like me down?

52:54.277 --> 52:55.778
Well, no.

53:00.074 --> 53:01.742
You look so good.

53:01.826 --> 53:05.037
Look, open that up.
Open it.

53:05.705 --> 53:06.831
For me?

53:06.914 --> 53:07.957
I think so.

53:09.208 --> 53:12.587
It's nothing much,
you know, nothing.

53:17.550 --> 53:19.051
See what's
written on the back?

53:19.135 --> 53:21.429
On the back? Aw.

53:22.388 --> 53:23.389
Always.

53:23.472 --> 53:26.309
"Always."
It's beautiful, Tony!

53:27.894 --> 53:29.979
Mama is still working
in the factory,

53:30.104 --> 53:32.231
and I work part-time
in a beauty parlor.

53:32.315 --> 53:35.401
I'm doing hair, Tony.
Do you remember Hiram Gonzalez?

53:35.651 --> 53:38.404
His father owned that barbershop.
It's his place.

53:38.487 --> 53:41.115
Plus I go to junior college.
Miami Dade.

53:41.282 --> 53:44.327
In two more years,
I get my cosmetology license.

53:44.410 --> 53:46.287
Then I'll be
making enough money...

53:46.370 --> 53:47.663
Surprise!

53:48.289 --> 53:51.000
All that's over,
starting today.

53:51.459 --> 53:52.501
Why?

53:52.585 --> 53:54.420
My kid sister
don't have to work

53:54.503 --> 53:57.256
in no beauty parlor,
and Mama,

53:57.840 --> 54:00.301
she don't have to
sew in no factory.

54:00.593 --> 54:02.678
Your son made it, Mama.

54:04.138 --> 54:05.473
He's a success.

54:06.641 --> 54:09.018
That's why I didn't
come around before.

54:09.977 --> 54:13.856
I want you to see what
a good boy I've been.

54:16.317 --> 54:17.777
Here's $1,000.

54:18.527 --> 54:19.987
For you, Mama.

54:27.828 --> 54:29.288
Who did you kill
for this, Antonio?

54:29.372 --> 54:30.498
Mama.

54:30.873 --> 54:32.833
I didn't kill nobody, Mama.

54:33.793 --> 54:34.877
No?
No.

54:35.878 --> 54:37.880
What are you doing now?

54:38.464 --> 54:41.550
Banks,
or is it still bodegas,
you and the others?

54:41.634 --> 54:43.886
No! Things are
different now.

54:43.970 --> 54:46.806
I'm working with
an anti-Castro group.

54:47.181 --> 54:48.808
I'm an organizer now.

54:48.891 --> 54:51.185
I get a lot of
political contributions.

54:52.228 --> 54:53.729
Sure you do.

54:58.067 --> 55:01.153
A gun sticking in
somebody's face is how.

55:02.780 --> 55:05.783
You know,
all we hear about in the papers

55:07.618 --> 55:10.579
is animals like you
and the killings.

55:11.288 --> 55:14.583
It's Cubans like you who are
giving a bad name to our people,

55:14.667 --> 55:16.335
people who come here,
work hard

55:16.419 --> 55:18.004
and make a good name
for themselves.

55:18.087 --> 55:20.047
People who send their
children to school.

55:20.131 --> 55:21.841
What are you saying?
That's your son...

55:21.924 --> 55:25.011
Son? I wish I had one.

55:25.845 --> 55:26.846
He's a bum.
No.

55:26.971 --> 55:29.807
He was a bum then
and he's a bum now.

55:31.809 --> 55:33.602
Who do you think
you are?

55:34.478 --> 55:35.604
Mmm?

55:36.147 --> 55:39.108
We haven't heard a word
from you in five years.

55:42.194 --> 55:44.905
You suddenly show up here,
throw some money around

55:44.989 --> 55:47.450
and think you
can get my respect.

55:48.034 --> 55:50.786
You think you can
buy me with jewelry?

55:50.870 --> 55:54.457
You think you can come into my
house with your hotshot clothes

55:54.540 --> 55:57.043
and your jail manners
and make fun of us?

55:57.126 --> 55:59.045
You don't know
what you're saying.

55:59.128 --> 56:01.297
That's not the way
I am, Antonio!

56:01.464 --> 56:03.966
That is not the way
I raised Gina to be!

56:06.135 --> 56:08.554
You are not
going to destroy her.

56:10.222 --> 56:11.974
I don't need
your money.

56:14.060 --> 56:15.895
I work for my living.

56:16.479 --> 56:19.023
I don't want you
in this house anymore!

56:19.482 --> 56:21.484
I don't want you
around Gina.

56:22.359 --> 56:25.071
So come on.
Get out!

56:31.243 --> 56:32.244
Okay.

56:35.748 --> 56:36.874
Mama...

56:36.957 --> 56:40.961
And take this lousy money
with you. It stinks.

56:41.212 --> 56:42.338
Tony.

56:43.672 --> 56:46.509
Why do you have to spoil
it for everybody, huh?

56:49.178 --> 56:50.846
I'm sorry, Tony.

56:52.556 --> 56:53.933
Okay, Mama.

56:58.229 --> 56:59.730
No. Tony,
wait a minute!

56:59.855 --> 57:00.898
Don't go, please!

57:00.981 --> 57:02.024
Gina, stay here!

57:02.233 --> 57:03.275
No, Mama.

57:03.359 --> 57:04.360
He's no good. Gina!

57:05.694 --> 57:07.530
Tony, wait, please!

57:08.114 --> 57:10.241
I'm sorry.
I don't know.

57:10.324 --> 57:12.576
Mama, ever since
Papa left, she's...

57:12.701 --> 57:14.870
Forget Papa.
We never had one.

57:15.037 --> 57:17.581
I know you did some
bad things back then.

57:17.873 --> 57:20.543
In the Army,
I know you got into some trouble.

57:20.626 --> 57:22.378
The Communists,

57:22.461 --> 57:24.547
they're always trying
to tell you what to do.

57:24.630 --> 57:26.173
Mama doesn't
understand that.

57:26.257 --> 57:27.466
I know.

57:29.093 --> 57:31.679
I just...
I don't know.

57:31.762 --> 57:34.390
I just want you to know
that I don't care.

57:34.640 --> 57:35.933
It doesn't matter
to me how long

57:36.016 --> 57:38.561
you've been away,
five or ten years.

57:40.604 --> 57:43.816
You're my blood, always.

57:45.025 --> 57:47.570
I know.

57:56.662 --> 57:58.664
Come on.
I want you to take this.

57:58.747 --> 57:59.832
I gotta go back in.

57:59.957 --> 58:01.208
No, Tony. Please.

58:01.292 --> 58:02.668
You need this.

58:02.751 --> 58:04.086
What will I tell her?

58:04.170 --> 58:05.921
Take that.
You don't tell her anything.

58:06.005 --> 58:07.339
Don't tell her
I gave it to you,

58:07.423 --> 58:09.550
but give her some
from time to time.

58:09.633 --> 58:12.261
And listen,
you go out yourself.

58:12.344 --> 58:15.764
Go ahead.
Go out, do some things.
Have some fun.

58:15.931 --> 58:18.100
You gotta get
some fun out of life.

58:18.184 --> 58:21.020
You gonna beat yourself
to death at 19?

58:21.103 --> 58:23.606
A pussycat like you?
Come here.

58:28.027 --> 58:29.904
I'll talk to you again.
Okay.

58:29.987 --> 58:32.114
Put that money away.
Don't let her see it.

58:32.198 --> 58:33.699
I'll talk to her.

58:35.618 --> 58:37.036
I'll talk to you.
Okay.

58:39.163 --> 58:40.247
Let's go.

58:42.249 --> 58:43.542
She's beautiful.
How come you...

58:43.626 --> 58:44.877
Hey!

58:47.338 --> 58:51.383
Stay away from her.
You hear?

58:52.176 --> 58:53.719
She's not for you.

58:53.802 --> 58:54.845
Okay.

59:20.329 --> 59:22.122
So, this and my
other factory,

59:22.206 --> 59:23.415
I can guarantee production

59:23.499 --> 59:27.586
of 200 kilos refined
every month of the year.

59:28.003 --> 59:30.256
The problem is,
I have no steady market.

59:30.339 --> 59:33.759
Basically, what I'm looking
for is somebody in the States

59:33.842 --> 59:36.053
who can share
the risk with me,

59:36.136 --> 59:37.263
somebody
who can guarantee

59:37.346 --> 59:41.517
to buy from me, say,
150 kilos a month.

59:41.934 --> 59:46.272
Oh, that's a big commitment, Mr. Sosa.
Something like that...

59:47.356 --> 59:49.692
Too bad Frank's not here.
You should talk to him.

59:49.775 --> 59:51.694
It would've been
nice if he'd come.

59:51.777 --> 59:52.861
He would like to come,

59:52.945 --> 59:55.114
but with his trial
coming up,

59:55.197 --> 59:57.533
it's hard to
leave the country.

59:57.616 --> 59:59.451
So he sent
you instead?

59:59.535 --> 01:00:01.036
Something like that.

01:00:01.120 --> 01:00:03.372
We'll talk at my house,
shall we?

01:00:03.998 --> 01:00:07.376
You got good stuff here.
Class-A shit.

01:00:29.231 --> 01:00:32.985
This Lopez guarantees
to buy 150 kilos from me

01:00:33.068 --> 01:00:34.403
every month
of the year.

01:00:34.486 --> 01:00:35.654
He picks it up here.

01:00:35.738 --> 01:00:38.032
I can sell it to him
for as little as

01:00:39.908 --> 01:00:43.412
7,000 a key.
You can't do better than that.

01:00:44.246 --> 01:00:47.082
But then we got to take
the risk of moving it.

01:00:47.249 --> 01:00:50.252
We'll be cutting out the Colombians.
Know what that means?

01:00:50.336 --> 01:00:52.254
That means we have to
go to war with them.

01:00:52.338 --> 01:00:55.924
We cut out the Colombians,
we take risks on both sides.

01:00:56.008 --> 01:00:57.885
Why don't we split the risk?

01:00:59.553 --> 01:01:03.098
You guarantee your delivery,
say, as far as Panama,

01:01:03.932 --> 01:01:05.684
we take it from there.

01:01:08.020 --> 01:01:11.440
Panama is risky.
It costs me more.

01:01:13.108 --> 01:01:17.363
Panama I can sell
for 13.5 a key.

01:01:18.614 --> 01:01:21.116
13.5?
What, are you nuts?

01:01:22.743 --> 01:01:26.372
13.5? We still got to
take that shit to Florida.

01:01:26.455 --> 01:01:28.540
Do you know what
that's like these days?

01:01:28.624 --> 01:01:30.751
You got the Navy everywhere.

01:01:30.918 --> 01:01:32.878
You got frogmen.

01:01:32.961 --> 01:01:35.255
You got EC2s with
the satellite-tracking shit.

01:01:35.881 --> 01:01:39.134
You got the fucking Bell 209
assault choppers up the ass.

01:01:39.635 --> 01:01:42.137
We're losing one
out of every nine loads.

01:01:43.097 --> 01:01:45.974
That's no duckwalk anymore,
let me tell you.

01:01:46.225 --> 01:01:47.643
Forget about 13.5.

01:01:51.230 --> 01:01:53.982
What do you suggest
that is reasonable?

01:01:59.571 --> 01:02:01.615
Excuse me.
One moment.

01:02:06.078 --> 01:02:08.414
What the fuck's
the matter with you?

01:02:08.497 --> 01:02:10.165
Are you negotiating
for Frank Lopez?

01:02:10.249 --> 01:02:12.501
Don't worry about it.
Take it easy.

01:02:12.584 --> 01:02:15.629
I'm not worried about it.
You should worry about it.

01:02:16.171 --> 01:02:19.007
If he wants to make a deal,
it's up to him, not you.

01:02:19.133 --> 01:02:20.676
We're doing this
one deal. That's it.

01:02:20.801 --> 01:02:22.678
Fuck you.
How's that?

01:02:23.846 --> 01:02:25.597
Fuck you.
Fuck you.

01:02:25.681 --> 01:02:28.434
You need to open your eyes
and keep your mouth shut.

01:02:28.517 --> 01:02:29.977
That's it.
Let it go at that.

01:02:30.060 --> 01:02:31.437
Don't worry about it.

01:02:31.520 --> 01:02:33.480
Your head's in
the wrong place.

01:02:33.564 --> 01:02:34.857
You must watch
out for yourself.

01:02:34.940 --> 01:02:36.108
Why not talk to him?

01:02:36.191 --> 01:02:38.193
You think he wants
to give you the money?

01:02:38.277 --> 01:02:39.695
Shut the fuck up.

01:02:39.820 --> 01:02:41.864
I'm doing
the talking here, not you.

01:02:42.698 --> 01:02:45.367
You're here to watch my back.
Watch my back.

01:02:46.827 --> 01:02:48.787
Better than your front,
let me tell you.

01:02:48.871 --> 01:02:50.372
That's easier to watch.

01:02:50.456 --> 01:02:51.874
Close your mouth.

01:02:52.207 --> 01:02:55.502
I can't wait to see what
Frank's gonna react to this one.

01:02:56.044 --> 01:02:58.672
Just shut up. I'm doing
the talking here.

01:02:59.882 --> 01:03:01.133
Now where were we?

01:03:01.216 --> 01:03:02.384
Panama.

01:03:02.843 --> 01:03:05.053
You're looking for
a partner, right?

01:03:06.430 --> 01:03:07.973
Something like that.

01:03:08.056 --> 01:03:11.560
Look, Mr. Sosa,
we're getting ahead of ourselves.

01:03:12.227 --> 01:03:16.773
I am down on Frank's authority
to buy 200 keys, that's it.

01:03:16.940 --> 01:03:18.984
That's my limit.
I got no right.

01:03:19.067 --> 01:03:20.277
Nobody got no right
to negotiate...

01:03:20.360 --> 01:03:22.154
Let the man
finish, okay?

01:03:22.237 --> 01:03:24.948
Let him propose a proposition,
then we can talk more.

01:03:25.073 --> 01:03:27.034
You got no
authority here.

01:03:27.117 --> 01:03:29.912
I started you in this
business, so shut the fuck up.

01:03:30.037 --> 01:03:32.456
Frank is gonna love it.

01:03:32.539 --> 01:03:34.041
That's up to Frank,
not you!

01:03:37.586 --> 01:03:39.630
I'm sorry about this,
Mr. Sosa.

01:03:40.088 --> 01:03:41.632
No, it is all right.

01:03:42.216 --> 01:03:45.427
You're right.
Maybe you should talk to Frank.

01:03:48.305 --> 01:03:49.431
Well, good.

01:03:50.766 --> 01:03:53.936
I don't think it's something I
want to do on an overseas phone.

01:03:54.228 --> 01:03:57.189
But as soon as
I get back to Miami,

01:03:57.272 --> 01:03:59.107
I will talk to
Frank personally.

01:04:00.275 --> 01:04:01.276
Good.

01:04:02.069 --> 01:04:04.446
My associates can
escort you to my chopper

01:04:04.571 --> 01:04:06.240
to take you
to Santa Cruz.

01:04:06.323 --> 01:04:09.409
I have a jet there.
You'll be in Miami in five hours.

01:04:09.493 --> 01:04:12.496
You'll be back here
tomorrow in time for lunch.

01:04:14.122 --> 01:04:15.541
Good.

01:04:19.002 --> 01:04:20.629
Good talking to you.

01:04:21.672 --> 01:04:23.799
Why not leave
your friend here?

01:04:23.924 --> 01:04:26.677
While you're gone,
he can tell me how
to run my business.

01:04:26.802 --> 01:04:28.470
I think Frank
wants to see him.

01:04:28.554 --> 01:04:29.846
No, that's okay.

01:04:29.972 --> 01:04:33.642
You tell Frank I'm keeping
this guy on ice for him.

01:04:36.395 --> 01:04:37.938
I guess so.

01:04:41.191 --> 01:04:43.026
Let's finish
our lunch.

01:04:47.531 --> 01:04:49.741
I have to hand it
to you, Mr. Sosa.

01:04:51.118 --> 01:04:53.370
You got everything
a man could want.

01:04:55.330 --> 01:04:58.125
I like you, Tony.
There is no lying in you.

01:04:59.710 --> 01:05:01.503
Unfortunately,
I don't feel the same

01:05:01.587 --> 01:05:03.880
about the rest of
your organization.

01:05:07.426 --> 01:05:09.678
What do you mean
by that, Mr. Sosa?

01:05:10.345 --> 01:05:12.764
I'm talking
about Omar Suarez.

01:05:15.475 --> 01:05:18.979
This garbage was recognized
by my associate at lunch

01:05:19.938 --> 01:05:22.316
from several years ago
in New York.

01:05:26.612 --> 01:05:28.739
He was an informer
for the police.

01:05:46.590 --> 01:05:50.886
He put Vito Duval and Nello
and Gino Ramos away for life.

01:05:55.474 --> 01:05:58.310
So how do I know you're not a
<i>chivato,</i> too, Tony?

01:06:01.730 --> 01:06:02.731
Hey, Sosa.

01:06:05.359 --> 01:06:07.611
Let's get this
straight now.

01:06:09.321 --> 01:06:13.492
I've never fucked anybody over
who didn't have it coming.

01:06:13.742 --> 01:06:15.118
You got that?

01:06:16.078 --> 01:06:19.873
All I have in this world
is my balls and my word.

01:06:19.998 --> 01:06:23.377
I don't break them for no
one, you understand?

01:06:24.503 --> 01:06:27.130
That piece of shit up
there, I never liked him,

01:06:27.214 --> 01:06:28.715
I never trusted him.

01:06:28.924 --> 01:06:30.926
For all I know,
he had me set up

